content: Would definitely be better if it had pronunciation guidance included in the entries too, not just separate page with it... Still, includes quite a bit of vocab and I know there's only so much established. It's easy to navigate and gave me more or less what I wanted.
Update: The app now has this feature! Awesome! Original review: Awesome app! It would be even nicer if the scroll wheel on the right allowed you to skip to a specific letter in the dictionary.
It has everything really and tells you pronunciation grammar and phrases so it makes elvish learnable

This app is great, however, it would be even better if it had a function where you can type words or phrases and it'll translate it. That way, it would become more diverse and better for learning the language
This app is amazing if you want to learn the language! Not sure if its correct but it's still awesome!
I wonder why the examples are Russian. Isn't English more common in this world?
It's a great app, I hope you keep improving it.
